text: EVERYONE HERE!!! WATCHING THIS TRAILER!!! I want you to do me a favor. I don't expect you to. I expect you to ignore this. I'm trying anyway. For those that have stopped for a second: Listen to the plot of this movie. Now, watch his comedy special:          https://youtu.be/vlEez-cmGa4 . You don't even have to watch the whole thing. Skip to -  23:39. I'm betting on the idea that if you stopped, you have at least some curiosity and hopefully an open mind. This video and this section in particular is about Dave Chappelle explaining why he went to Africa all those years ago. Some of you may have never heard about that or don't even know Chappelle. What is important is that he says that he can't talk about why he left directly so he explains it with a story. A story from a book. A story not unlike this plot. Try to ignore the jokes and the laughter. Try to remember that this is a story explaining why he went to Africa. If you're still with me, look up Patrice O'Neal and see what he said about owing someone. Something in someone's drink. Now, maybe the well is running dry on original ideas or action dramas have typical narratives that we see all the time. But what do these narratives have to do with Dave Chappelle's story and why are they so similar? What does Dave Chappelle have in common with the movie industry? Or Patrice O'Neal. Maybe nothing.
